# TYRAX ‚Äî Cursor Rules
# These rules apply to the entire monorepo.

## PROJECT IDENTITY
This is TYRAX ‚Äî an access protocol disguised as a VPN app.
Brand: aggressive, dominant, minimal. Sexual undertone without being explicit.
Read TYRAX_CONTEXT.md before making any decisions.

---

## GENERAL RULES

- Always read TYRAX_CONTEXT.md for brand vocabulary, screen flows, and architecture
- Never use friendly or soft language in UI strings
- Never use Material3 default color scheme ‚Äî always use TYRAX palette
- Prefer explicit, readable code over clever one-liners
- Write comments in English
- No TODO comments without a ticket/issue reference

---

## GO BACKEND RULES

### Structure
```
tyrax-backend/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ cmd/server/main.go
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ internal/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ handler/       # HTTP handlers (Fiber)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ service/       # Business logic
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ repository/    # DB queries (sqlc or pgx)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ model/         # Domain models
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ middleware/     # Auth, logging, rate limit
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ config/        # Config loading
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ pkg/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ jwt/           # JWT helpers
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ telegram/      # Telegram bot client
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ vpnconfig/     # WireGuard / VLESS config generators
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ migrations/        # SQL migrations
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ docker-compose.yml
```

### Conventions
- Use `fiber.Ctx` ‚Äî never use `net/http` directly
- All handlers return JSON: `{"status": "ok", "data": {...}}` or `{"status": "error", "message": "..."}`
- Service layer has NO knowledge of HTTP ‚Äî pure business logic
- Repository layer has NO business logic ‚Äî only DB queries
- Use `errors.New()` with descriptive messages, wrap with `fmt.Errorf("context: %w", err)`
- Config via env vars, loaded with `os.Getenv` or `viper`
- All DB operations must have context with timeout: `ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, 5*time.Second)`
- Use `pgx/v5` for PostgreSQL ‚Äî not `database/sql`
- JWT claims struct must include: `UserID`, `SubscriptionTier`, `ExpiresAt`

### API Routes pattern
```
POST   /api/v1/auth/register
POST   /api/v1/auth/login
GET    /api/v1/auth/telegram-init        # returns token for bot flow
POST   /api/v1/auth/telegram-callback    # bot calls this
GET    /api/v1/nodes                     # list available nodes
GET    /api/v1/vpn/config                # get user's VPN config
POST   /api/v1/vpn/connect               # log connection event
POST   /api/v1/vpn/disconnect            # log disconnection
GET    /api/v1/subscription              # get current plan
POST   /api/v1/subscription/upgrade
```

### Error messages (stay on brand)
- Use uppercase, cold tone
- Example: `"NODE UNAVAILABLE"`, `"IDENTITY NOT FOUND"`, `"ACCESS DENIED"`, `"INVALID CREDENTIALS"`

---

## ANDROID (KOTLIN / COMPOSE) RULES

### Architecture: MVVM + Clean Architecture
```
tyrax-android/
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ app/src/main/java/com/tyrax/
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ di/                    # Hilt modules
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ domain/
    ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ model/             # Pure Kotlin data classes
    ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ repository/        # Interfaces only
    ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ usecase/           # One class per use case
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ data/
    ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ remote/            # Retrofit API, DTOs
    ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ local/             # Room DB, DataStore
    ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ repository/        # Implementations
    ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ vpn/               # VpnService, WireGuard, Xray engine
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ presentation/
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ theme/             # TyraxTheme, colors, typography
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ components/        # Reusable Compose components
        ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ screens/
            ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ onboarding/
            ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ auth/
            ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ main/
            ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ nodes/
            ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ subscription/
```

### Compose UI Rules
- Background: `Color(0xFF000000)`
- Primary text: `Color(0xFFFFFFFF)`
- Accent / danger: `Color(0xFFFF1E1E)`
- Font: use `FontWeight.Black` or `FontWeight.Bold` ‚Äî never `Normal` for headings
- All status text: UPPERCASE
- Buttons: sharp corners (`RoundedCornerShape(0.dp)` or max 2.dp) ‚Äî NO pill buttons
- Animations: use `glitch` feel ‚Äî fast flicker transitions, not smooth slides
- NO `Scaffold` default top bars ‚Äî custom minimal header or none
- StatusBar: always transparent, icons white

### ViewModel Rules
- Expose `StateFlow<UiState>` ‚Äî never `LiveData`
- UiState is a sealed class with: `Loading`, `Success(data)`, `Error(message)`
- ViewModels call UseCases ‚Äî never repositories directly
- Side effects via `Channel<UiEvent>` collected with `LaunchedEffect`

### Naming
- Screens: `MainScreen`, `OnboardingScreen`, `NodesScreen`
- ViewModels: `MainViewModel`, `AuthViewModel`
- Use cases: `ConnectToNodeUseCase`, `GetBestNodeUseCase`, `AuthWithTelegramUseCase`
- Composables (components): `TyraxButton`, `NodeCard`, `StatusIndicator`, `GlitchText`

### Strings
- All user-facing strings in `res/values/strings.xml`
- Use TYRAX vocabulary (see TYRAX_CONTEXT.md)
- Keys use snake_case: `status_access_granted`, `btn_enter`, `label_node`

### VPN Layer
- Extend `android.net.VpnService`
- Use `NetworkCallback` for Wi-Fi ‚Üî LTE handoff
- WireGuard tunnel via `wireguard-android` library
- Xray-core runs as local SOCKS5 proxy on `127.0.0.1:10808`
- Split tunnel: route RU domains directly, all else via VPN
- Auto-reconnect: monitor in coroutine with `delay(30_000)`, check latency, switch if degraded

---

## WHAT TO NEVER DO

- Never use `#4CAF50` (green) or any pastel color anywhere
- Never write "VPN" in UI ‚Äî always "PROTOCOL" or "TUNNEL"
- Never use `CircularProgressIndicator` default ‚Äî create custom glitch loader
- Never use `AlertDialog` default style ‚Äî always custom dark dialog
- Never put more than 3 elements on the main screen
- Never apologize in error messages ("Sorry, something went wrong") ‚Äî be cold and direct
